&lt;p&gt;Where traditional roles escalate or hand off, you execute. Where others identify problems, you own the full path to resolution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll become deeply fluent in how different clinic types operate, translating clinical and operational workflows (intake, scheduling, staffing, billing, reporting) into scalable technical implementations. Your work will directly shape both customer outcomes and the evolution of the core platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a “solutions consulting” or coordination-heavy role. You will write production-grade code, build and maintain integrations, debug production issues in customer environments, and contribute to architectural decisions based on what you learn in the field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Technical Outcomes Across Customer Implementations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end technical execution for key clinic partners during implementation and post-launch optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex clinical and operational workflows into scalable technical designs and implement them directly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain integrations across customer systems (EHRs, scheduling, billing, data pipelines), ensuring reliability and correctness in real-world usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve gaps between intended platform configuration and actual customer performance through hands-on engineering work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eliminate Friction and Accelerate Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical owner for complex customer issues that would otherwise require coordination across multiple internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make fast, independent decisions on implementation approach by developing deep fluency in platform architecture and configuration patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reusable technical patterns (integration templates, workflow modules, deployment playbooks) that improve speed and consistency across customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
